description: Hybrid solver for general BQM problems
Hybrid solver for general DQM problems

parameters.anneal_offsets: Anneal offsets for each working qubit, formatted as a list, with NaN specified for unused qubits.
parameters.anneal_schedule: Annealing schedule formatted as a piecewise linear list of floating-point pairs of 't' and 's'.
parameters.annealing_time: Quantum annealing duration, in microseconds, as a positive floating point number.
parameters.answer_mode: Format of returned answers, as 'histogram' or 'raw' samples.
parameters.auto_scale: Automatic rescaling of h and J values to their available range, as a boolean flag.
parameters.flux_biases: Flux biases for each working qubit, in normalized offset units, formatted as a list for all qubits.
parameters.flux_drift_compensation: Activation of flux drift compensation, as a boolean flag.
parameters.h_gain_schedule: h-gain schedule formatted as a piecewise linear list of floating-point pairs of 't' and 'g'.
parameters.initial_state: Initial states to use for a reverse-anneal request, as a list of qubit index and state.
parameters.max_answers: Maximum number of answers to return.
parameters.num_reads: Number of states to read (answers to return), as a positive integer.
parameters.programming_thermalization: Time in microseconds to wait after programming the processor in order for it to cool back to base temperature, as a positive floating point number.
parameters.readout_thermalization: Time in microseconds to wait after each state is read from the processor in order for it to cool back to base temperature, as a positive floating point number.
parameters.reduce_intersample_correlation: Addition of pauses between samples, as a boolean flag.
parameters.reinitialize_state: Reapplication of the initial_state for every read in reverse annealing, as a boolean flag.
parameters.fast_anneal: Activation of the fast-anneal protocol, as a boolean flag.
